header.gameNote: JIM THORPE CLASSIC AT CINCINNATI OH

article.headline: High Point 81, Howard 62
article.story: CINCINNATI (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 21 points to lead High Point to an 81-62 victory over Howard in the Jim Thorpe Classic on Saturday night. Cincinnati beat Tennessee-Martin 67-49 in the early game of the exempted, round-robin tournament. Mike Jefferson had 15 points for High Point (1-1), and Jerald Minnis had 12. Darryl Hudson led Howard (0-2) with 17 points, and Eugene Myatt and Will Gant had 12 apiece. High Point was 49 percent from the field (32-of-65), and Howard was 43 percent (22-of-51).
